            <h2>The Mission</h2>
            <p>Welcome to <strong>Using Sports as a Day Trading Job</strong>. I created this blog to document my journey in treating sports markets with the same rigor, discipline, and analytical depth as traditional financial markets.</p>
            
            <p>I believe that sports betting is often misunderstood as "gambling." In reality, it is a liquid marketplace where information is currency and price discovery happens in real-time. My goal is to find <strong>Alpha</strong> by identifying market inefficiencies before the whistle blows.</p>

            <h3>The Strategy</h3>
            <p>My approach is rooted in three core pillars:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Bankroll Management:</strong> Using the Kelly Criterion to protect capital.</li>
                <li><strong>Closing Line Value (CLV):</strong> Consistently beating the market price.</li>
                <li><strong>Emotional Neutrality:</strong> Trading based on data, never on fandom.</li>
            </ul>

